The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for maritime anomaly detection and vessel route prediction using data collected by the Automatic Identification System (AIS). This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the construction of a standardized AIS database for trajectory learning and data mining, which could fall under the sub-categories of Databases (cs.DB) and Software Engineering (cs.SE).
